Earlier this month, in front of a packed
audience of awards season voters at The Brownstone in Los Angeles, four of =
Puck=E2=80=99s A-list journalists=E2=80=94Matthew Belloni, Lauren Sherman, =
Peter Hamby, and Baratunde Thurston=E2=80=94took the stage to conduct a ser=
ies of intimate conversations with a slate of the season=E2=80=99s most dis=
tinguished filmmakers, costume designers, and actors.=C2=A0

The premise of Puck=E2=80=99s inaugural Stories of the Season event was to =
elevate the
often dry and predictable awards season conversation series, and whether it=
 was Peter=E2=80=99s riveting conversation with actors Jeremy Strong, Zoe S=
alda=C3=B1a, and Peter Sarsgaard, or Matt Belloni=E2=80=99s keynote convers=
ations with up-and-coming star Mikey Madison and Dune director Denis Villen=
euve, the evening more than delivered on that promise. If you weren=E2=80=
=99t able to attend, you can
watch video replays of the panel conversations by clicking on the links bel=
ow. The evening was presented in partnership with Polestar, and supported b=
y Mayer Brown, Wondery, and HBO and Max.

